From: Wang Xingchao <xingchao.wang@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 7 Jun 2012 16:51:33 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 071/129] ALSA: hda - reduce msleep time if EPSS power states
 supported

upstream: 0f4ccbb02533276ab750961e150aeee06492ed7c

if EPSS supported, transition from D3 state to D0 state in less
than 10ms

Signed-off-by: Wang Xingchao <xingchao.wang@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Signed-off-by: fupan li <fupan.li@windriver.com>
---
 sound/pci/hda/hda_codec.c |    7 +++++--
 1 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/pci/hda/hda_codec.c b/sound/pci/hda/hda_codec.c
index 51a8e34..4530175 100644
--- a/sound/pci/hda/hda_codec.c
+++ b/sound/pci/hda/hda_codec.c
@@ -3473,8 +3473,11 @@ static void hda_set_power_state(struct hda_codec *codec, hda_nid_t fg,
 	}
 
 	/* this delay seems necessary to avoid click noise at power-down */
-	if (power_state == AC_PWRST_D3)
-		msleep(100);
+	if (power_state == AC_PWRST_D3) {
+		/* transition time less than 10ms for power down */
+		bool epss = snd_hda_codec_get_supported_ps(codec, fg, AC_PWRST_EPSS);
+		msleep(epss ? 10 : 100);
+	}
 	snd_hda_codec_read(codec, fg, 0, AC_VERB_SET_POWER_STATE,
 			    power_state);
 	snd_hda_codec_set_power_to_all(codec, fg, power_state, true);
